impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Jenna, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Janice': 'Kathryn', 'Jenna': 'Doris', 'Jeffrey': 'Doris'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Janice', 'Jenna', 'Jeffrey']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 2\n - Final Target: Doris\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nDoris's speech: Hello everyone, my name is Doris, and I am the Guard. Last night, I protected Gerald, and I can assure you that he is safe. Tonight, I will protect another player, but I will not reveal their name to avoid any suspicion. My role is to keep the village safe, and I am committed to fulfilling this responsibility. I hope that by protecting key players, we can identify and eliminate the werewolves. Let's work together to ensure the survival of our village.\nGerald's speech: Thank you, Doris, for protecting me last night. Your dedication to the village's safety is greatly appreciated. As for me, I have been observing the players closely and have noticed some concerning behavior from Janice. I believe she may be a werewolf based on my observations. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. We need to stay vigilant and make informed decisions to ensure the survival of our village.\nJanice's speech: Thank you, Doris, for your dedication to keeping our village safe. I appreciate your efforts and the trust you place in me. Regarding Gerald's accusation, I want to address it directly. I have been observing the players closely, and I believe that Gerald's behavior is more suspicious than mine. He has been making accusations without providing any concrete evidence, which makes me question his motives. I am a villager, and my goal is to help identify and eliminate the werewolves. I have been working hard to gather information and protect key players, and I will continue to do so. Let's focus on the facts and make informed decisions to ensure the survival of our village.\nJeffrey's speech: Thank you, Doris, for your dedication to keeping our village safe. I have also been observing the players closely, and I have not noticed any suspicious behavior from Janice. I agree with you that we need to focus on the facts and make informed decisions. Your role as the Guard is crucial, and I support your efforts to protect key players. Let's work together to ensure the survival of our village. I suggest that we continue to protect important players and investigate any suspicious behavior. Who do you think we should protect tonight, and who should we investigate further?\nJenna's speech: Thank you, Doris, for your dedication to keeping our village safe. Your role as the Guard is crucial, and I support your efforts to protect key players. I agree with Jeffrey that we need to focus on the facts and gather more information before making accusations. Let's not jump to conclusions without evidence. Instead, let's continue to protect important players and investigate any suspicious behavior. Who do you think we should protect tonight, and who should we investigate further?\nJenna's speech: Thank you, Doris, for your dedication to keeping our village safe. Your role as the Guard is crucial, and I support your efforts to protect key players. I agree with Jeffrey that we need to focus on the facts and gather more information before making accusations. Let's not jump to conclusions without evidence. Instead, let's c